article.headline: Tulane 77, Savannah State 61
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Wayne Tinsley's 13 points led four Tulane players in double figures as the Green Wave defeated Savannah State 77-61 on Saturday night. Tinsley also grabbed 12 rebounds and had seven assists in getting his third straight double-double. Marcus Kinzer scored 15 points for Tulane (7-8), while Quincy Davis added 11 and Vytas Tatarunas had 10. Davis also added eight rebounds and a career-high seven blocked shots. Donald Carson scored 20 points and Sherard Reddick 10 for Savannah State (1-20), which never could get closer than seven points in the second half. Josh Barker's three-pointer cut Savannah State's deficit to 54-47 with 10:57 to go, but Tulane's Chris Moore answered with a three-pointer of his own. Michael Mitchell's jumper made it 58-51 with 8:49 left, but Tinsley scored on a fast break layup and a breakaway dunk to push the advantage back to double figures. The Wave led by as many as 14 in the first half and held a 42-30 advantage at halftime. <
